# Writing style
- Never use em dashes in any output: code, comments, commit messages, PR descriptions, or chat replies. Use a regular dash, parentheses, or split the sentence instead.

# Workflow skills
The detailed playbooks for the most common tasks live in `.claude/skills/` and are auto-discovered by the Skill tool. Read the skill's `SKILL.md` and follow it when you reach the matching phase. Do not paraphrase or duplicate skill content here.

- `record-browser-video` - script-driven before/after recordings against the live Rancher (CDP, hover->wait->click pattern, deferred recording).
- `create-commit` - concise commit on a new `issue-$(issueNumber)` branch, no AI co-author.
- `create-pr` - push and open a draft PR upstream. Includes the **Playwright + CDP upload flow** that posts videos and screenshots to GitHub `user-attachments` so they embed inline in the PR body.
- `review-pr` - pending inline review comments only, never submit.

# Fix Issue
- Review the issue and attempt to solve it.
- **Before using the browser (playwright/CDP) or hitting Rancher, run `wait-for-sidecars`.** The sidecar containers may
not be running yet. This script starts them if needed and blocks until CDP and the Rancher API actually respond.
Skipping it means DNS errors and empty videos/screenshots.
- Reproduce the issue against the live Rancher and record a before video. Follow the `record-browser-video` skill.
- Write a detailed reproduction description and, if needed, create supporting resources in the Rancher instance so
someone else could reproduce it from the same starting state.
- Record an after video demonstrating the fix. Same skill.
- Take screenshots with `browser.mjs screenshot` at any point to highlight changed areas; save them under
`/workspace/screenshots/`.
- When the fix is committed and ready for review, follow the `create-commit` skill, then `create-pr` (which uploads media to GitHub for you).
